<%# views/privacypolicy.ejs %>
<%- include("partials/header", {
  pageTitle: "Privacy Policy",
  activeNav: "privacy-policy",
  pageClass: "privacy-policy-page",
  pageStyles: ["/styles/privacypolicy.css"],
  metaDescription: "Read the Privacy Policy for The Accountability Report Podcast, including current website privacy practices and planned future handling of contact and story-tip information."
}) %>

<section class="privacy-policy-hero" aria-labelledby="privacy-policy-page-title">
  <div class="site-container privacy-policy-hero__content">
    <span class="privacy-policy-kicker">Policy</span>

    <h1 id="privacy-policy-page-title" class="privacy-policy-hero__title">
      Privacy Policy
    </h1>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="privacy-policy-content" aria-labelledby="privacy-policy-content-title">
  <div class="site-container privacy-policy-content__inner">
    <h2 id="privacy-policy-content-title" class="screen-reader-text">
      Privacy Policy details
    </h2>

    <article class="privacy-policy-copy">
      <p class="privacy-policy-lead">
        This Privacy Policy explains how The Accountability Report Podcast handles website
        information, contact information, story tip descriptions, documentation descriptions,
        and user communications. Until public submission features are formally activated,
        visitors should not submit sensitive personal information through public forms.
      </p>

      <div class="privacy-policy-note">
        <p>
          A finalized Privacy Policy should be reviewed before any story tip submission,
          contact form, document upload, newsletter, analytics package, or database-backed
          intake feature becomes active.
        </p>
      </div>

      <section class="privacy-policy-section">
        <h2>1. Current Website Status</h2>

        <p>
          The Accountability Report Podcast website is currently being developed as an
          informational public-interest media website. Some forms, contact features, story
          tip features, and submission tools may appear as design placeholders before they
          are connected to a live review process.
        </p>

        <p>
          Visitors should treat inactive forms as non-operational. The website should not
          be used to submit passwords, Social Security numbers, full account numbers, medical
          records, financial credentials, private legal documents, security codes, or other
          sensitive personal information.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="privacy-policy-section">
        <h2>2. Information We May Collect</h2>

        <p>
          Once active, the website may collect information that a visitor voluntarily provides,
          such as a name, email address, topic category, date of incident, concern summary,
          supporting documentation description, correction request, general inquiry, or other
          communication submitted through an approved website process.
        </p>

        <p>
          The website may also process limited technical information needed to operate,
          secure, troubleshoot, or improve the website, such as browser type, device type,
          general request information, date and time of access, referral information, and
          server log information.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="privacy-policy-section">
        <h2>3. Story Tips and Documentation Descriptions</h2>

        <p>
          Story tip submission features are not active until privacy, storage, review,
          retention, and safety procedures are finalized. When activated, story tip
          submissions may be reviewed for editorial relevance, documentation value,
          public-interest value, and possible future reporting.
        </p>

        <p>
          Submitting a story tip does not guarantee publication, investigation, response,
          legal advice, agency action, or confidential treatment. Visitors should not submit
          unnecessary private identifiers or sensitive records through any public-facing form.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="privacy-policy-section">
        <h2>4. How Information May Be Used</h2>

        <p>
          Information submitted through approved website channels may be used to review
          public-interest concerns, respond to inquiries, evaluate correction requests,
          organize documentation, improve website content, prepare podcast topics, assess
          editorial relevance, and maintain website security.
        </p>

        <p>
          The podcast may summarize or discuss submitted concerns only when appropriate
          editorial review has been completed and when the presentation is consistent with
          privacy, safety, documentation, and public-interest standards.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="privacy-policy-section">
        <h2>5. Information Sharing</h2>

        <p>
          The Accountability Report Podcast does not intend to sell personal information.
          Information may be shared only when needed for website operation, legal compliance,
          safety review, editorial review, professional consultation, service-provider support,
          or when the visitor gives permission.
        </p>

        <p>
          If a matter appears to involve immediate danger, unlawful conduct, or a legal
          obligation, information may be reviewed or handled according to the circumstances
          and applicable procedures.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="privacy-policy-section">
        <h2>6. Sensitive Information</h2>

        <p>
          Visitors should not submit sensitive personal information unless a secure process
          is later activated and clearly explained. Sensitive information may include passwords,
          Social Security numbers, full account numbers, security codes, private medical
          information, private financial records, private legal documents, or unrelated
          personal information.
        </p>

        <p>
          If sensitive information is received unintentionally, it may be minimized, redacted,
          excluded from editorial use, or deleted where appropriate.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="privacy-policy-section">
        <h2>7. Data Storage and Retention</h2>

        <p>
          Before any active intake process is launched, the website should define how submitted
          information is stored, who may review it, how long it may be retained, how status
          changes are tracked, and how unnecessary information may be reduced or removed.
        </p>

        <p>
          Future storage may include a controlled database for public tip submissions, review
          status history, and editorial notes. No live database-backed story tip storage should
          be activated until privacy and review procedures are finalized.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="privacy-policy-section">
        <h2>8. Security</h2>

        <p>
          Reasonable administrative, technical, and organizational safeguards should be used
          to protect website operations and submitted information. No website, email system,
          database, or online submission process can guarantee absolute security.
        </p>

        <p>
          Visitors should avoid submitting sensitive information through ordinary web forms
          or email unless a secure process is later announced and clearly explained.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="privacy-policy-section">
        <h2>9. External Links and Platforms</h2>

        <p>
          The website may reference third-party websites, podcast platforms, public resources,
          agencies, social media platforms, or external documents. Third-party websites and
          services are controlled by their own privacy practices and terms.
        </p>

        <p>
          The Accountability Report Podcast is not responsible for the privacy practices,
          content, or security of external websites that are not controlled by the podcast.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="privacy-policy-section">
        <h2>10. Contact and Updates</h2>

        <p>
          Domain-based contact addresses are planned for official public communication once
          active. Privacy-related questions, correction requests, and formal communications
          should use official domain-based addresses after they are published.
        </p>

        <p>
          This Privacy Policy may be updated as the website, podcast, contact process, story
          tip review procedure, database structure, and publication workflow continue to develop.
        </p>
      </section>

      <aside class="privacy-policy-closing-note" aria-label="Privacy policy status">
        <p>
          Until the final privacy process is complete, public forms should remain inactive
          and should not collect sensitive personal information.
        </p>
      </aside>
    </article>
  </div>
</section>

<%- include("partials/footer") %>